SIMPLE: inexhaustible
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Inexhaustible
<hw>In`ex*haust"i*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Incapable of
being exhausted, emptied, or used up; unfailing; not to be wasted or
spent; <as>as, <ex>inexhaustible</ex> stores of provisions; an
<ex>inexhaustible</ex> stock of elegant words.</as></def>
<rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>An <qex>inexhaustible</qex> store of anecdotes.</q>
<rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>In`ex*haust"i*ble*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos> --
<wf>In`ex*haust"i*bly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inexhaustive</ent>⟦br⟧
